Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: 515 Crocker Street is part of the larger Downtown Industrial District in the Central City East region. This industrial pocket of Central Los Angeles experienced an average annual rental growth rate of 8% in the period of 2014 to 2019. Industrial buildings in downtown Los Angeles have historically experienced high occupancy rates and growing rental rates due to limited supply and rising demand.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is offering to qualified buyers the opportunity to purchase a ±9,386 SF industrial building in the Central City East area of Downtown Los Angeles for owner-user occupancy, lease up, or redevelopment. The site is in a California-and U.S. Government-recognized Opportunity Zone (OZ) and a City of Los Angeles Building Improvement District (BID). The property is unencumbered by lease or mortgage and is offered “as-is, where-is, with all faults.”
